---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="UK Elections" description="Election intelligence for every UK contest. Candidates, history, forecasts, source notes, and honest backtests.">
  <section class="hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Public election intelligence</p>
    <h1>Every contest, source-led and testable.</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      UK Elections is being built as a public record of candidates, boundaries, historic results,
      forecast probabilities, confidence intervals, and backtests across UK elections.
    </p>
    <div class="action-row" aria-label="Primary actions">
      <a class="button primary" href="/seats/">Review the seat model</a>
      <a class="button" href="/data-quality/">Check data quality</a>
      <a class="button" href="/methodology/">Read the method</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="status-grid" aria-label="Build status">
    <article>
      <span class="status-label">Repository</span>
      <strong>Live</strong>
      <p>GitHub is connected and deploying the static scaffold from the main branch.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <span class="status-label">Cloudflare Pages</span>
      <strong>Live</strong>
      <p>The production domain is bought and ready to attach once nameservers finish moving to Cloudflare.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <span class="status-label">Data ingestion</span>
      <strong>Queued</strong>
      <p>Candidate, result, boundary, polling, and demographic ingestion are specified before any forecast claims go public.</p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-head">
      <p class="eyebrow">Model scope</p>
      <h2>Build the rails before publishing numbers.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-list">
      <article>
        <h3>Local contests</h3>
        <p>Borough, county, and unitary elections use separate ward or division baselines, candidate gates, and boundary checks.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h3>National seats</h3>
        <p>Westminster, Senedd, and Scottish Parliament models need voting-system-specific allocation and transparent assumptions.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h3>Backtests</h3>
        <p>Every model release needs an archive of past predictions, error metrics, and missed-call analysis.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h3>Boundary history</h3>
        <p>Ward, division, constituency, and list geography changes are versioned before historical results are reused.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
